cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LO, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with finite automata running on infinite words.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents an algorithm for constructing finite-state independent normal words.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with the concept of independence in sequences.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses B\"uchi automata, which are commonly studied in this field.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper mentions the computational complexity of the algorithm for constructing finite-state independent normal words.
